      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Victorian mare ISTHISJUSTFANTASY (6) has been far from disgraced when tackling good opposition from tough draws of late. She is a two time winner at the mile and is nicely placed in this line up. SOHO GUNSLINGER (3) has been good from wider draws of late, racing parked but proving too good here two back before a solid second last time. His record at this circuit and distance stands at four from nine and he draws well. DANCE WITH CARMER (7) came from a similar barrier to this when winning here last week. Back in trip but came from wider to win over this distance earlier in the campaign. Must respect. The ace draw should serve FRANCO NOVELIST NZ (1) well. He is building in fitness and could be ready to win after a second at this circuit and distance last week.",
